&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maternity Assessment Unit Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;John Radcliffe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 Year Fixed Contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Band 7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the maternity service at Oxford University Hospital’s NHS Foundation Trust for an exceptional, committed and motivated midwife for the post of Maternity Assessment Unit Manager at the John Radcliffe Womens Centre. This is an excellent opportunity to develop your managerial skills. The individual will work closely with the Clinical Midwifery Manager/Consultant Midwife and Obstetric lead for Intrapartum Services to ensure excellent care is provided to the women and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Maternity Assessment Unit is a fast paced triage department which accepts referrals direct from women, community midwives, GP’s and antenatal clinics. It offers a varied workload and the succesful applicant will be expected to be able to work under pressure without compromising care. This is a leadership role and therefore the succesful applicant will be expected to have a strong clinical prescence. You will be expected to manage your time equally between clincal and managerial responsabilities. In return we would offer execellent managerial support and commitment to your professional growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The individual must have a strong commitment to midwifery practice, safety and have excellent organisational and leadership skills. The successful candidate will provide clinical leadership ensuring the team philosophy which promotes and reflects optimal standards of care for pregnant women and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in applying for the post we would welcome your application. If you wish to discuss the post or find out further information please contact: The post is Monday to Friday 08:00 until 16:00, this will include one clinical shift per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Laura Jones, Maternity Assessment Unit Manager Jones@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hazel Threlfall, Clinical Midwifery Manager. Threlfall@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 09-Nov-2020 08:00am&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
